# Concrete Strength Prediction

## Overview

Concrete compressive strength is one of the most important properties in construction engineering. The strength of concrete depends on various factors such as cement content, water ratio, fly ash, aggregates, and curing age.

This project uses Machine Learning regression techniques to predict concrete compressive strength based on its ingredients and age.

## Problem Statement

Develop a regression model capable of predicting the compressive strength of concrete mixtures using material composition and curing age.

## Dataset Information

The dataset contains:

* 1030 observations
* 8 input variables
* 1 target variable

Input Features:

* Cement
* Blast Furnace Slag
* Fly Ash
* Water
* Superplasticizer
* Coarse Aggregate
* Fine Aggregate
* Age

Target Variable:

* Concrete Compressive Strength (MPa)

